    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-11T17:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-11T17:36:00-05:00" n="882"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d882">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.602/10: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chase</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-11T17:00:00-05:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 12—3:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Reliably informed that Costa Rican Congress this afternoon passed the law
                    annulling Tinoco contracts, etc., referred to in last paragraph my August 3, 1
                    p.m. over the veto by more than two thirds. This includes Amory concession.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chase</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
